{# Prerequisites #}
<div class="ndx-walkthrough-prerequisites">
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Before you start</h2>

  <div class="govuk-warning-text">
    <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
    <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
      <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Important</span>
      You must have already requested the Minute AI scenario via NDX:Try.
    </strong>
  </div>

  <p class="govuk-body">
    <a href="/scenarios/minute/" class="govuk-link">Deploy the Minute AI scenario</a> if you haven't already.
  </p>

  <div class="govuk-warning-text">
    <span class="govuk-warning-text__icon" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
    <strong class="govuk-warning-text__text">
      <span class="govuk-visually-hidden">Important</span>
      Deployment takes 25 to 35 minutes. This provisions an Aurora PostgreSQL database, ECS Fargate services, and CloudFront distribution.
    </strong>
  </div>

  <details class="govuk-details govuk-!-margin-bottom-4">
    <summary class="govuk-details__summary">
      <span class="govuk-details__summary-text">Why does deployment take this long?</span>
    </summary>
    <div class="govuk-details__text">
      <p class="govuk-body">Minute AI provisions enterprise-grade infrastructure:</p>
      <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
        <li><strong>Aurora PostgreSQL database</strong> -- stores meetings, transcripts, and generated minutes</li>
        <li><strong>ECS Fargate services</strong> -- runs the web application and background workers</li>
        <li><strong>SQS queues</strong> -- manages transcription and minute generation jobs</li>
        <li><strong>CloudFront distribution</strong> -- provides secure HTTPS access</li>
        <li><strong>S3 bucket</strong> -- stores uploaded audio files</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
        The wait is worth it -- you get a fully functional AI meeting minute tool to evaluate.
      </p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <div class="govuk-inset-text">
    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      <strong>While you wait:</strong> Explore the CloudFormation Events tab to watch resources being created.
      You can also browse other areas of the AWS Console -- deployment continues in the background.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">You'll need</h3>
  <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>Your CloudFormation stack to show <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">CREATE_COMPLETE</span></li>
    <li>The <strong>MinuteUrl</strong> from your stack's Outputs tab</li>
    <li>The <strong>BasicAuthUsername</strong> and <strong>BasicAuthPassword</strong> from Outputs</li>
    <li>A meeting recording in MP3, WAV, or WebM format (any short recording will work)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

